id: pm-x6jf
title: "Promote package & extension lifecycle primitives to the public SDK: install, upgrade, extension list/enable/disable, managed-package state"
description: "Promote package and extension lifecycle operations into the public SDK so custom PM tools can install, upgrade, activate, deactivate, inspect, and manage packages without shelling out to CLI-only internals."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: architecture,"area:extensions","area:sdk"
created_at: "2026-07-06T21:58:30.613Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T18:22:33.141Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-14T18:08:27.801Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: "SDK exports typed primitives for package install/upgrade and extension lifecycle (list, enable/disable, managed-extensions state) returning the same structured results the CLI renders; pm install/upgrade/extension/package commands consume only these primitives; docstrings + linked tests + SDK reference docs; zero behavior change (install/extension specs green)"
parent: pm-usfg
risk: medium
confidence: medium
resolution: "Completed the public package lifecycle family and its remaining dynamic host contracts across SDK, CLI, tests, and author documentation."
expected_result: Custom PM tools and packages manage lifecycle and own dynamic command input/output through typed public SDK primitives.
actual_result: "Lifecycle primitives were previously promoted incrementally while the remaining list parsing, output ownership, renderer parity, and passthrough contracts lacked a complete verified boundary."
