comments[17]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-07T08:58:08.753Z",codex-agent,"Progress evidence: active PR bundle includes package/extension doctor isolation as a package-lifecycle primitive slice. Runtime loader options, CLI flags, SDK flag/tool contracts, shell completions, docs, and regression tests are being verified through pm-6abs; this item remains broader than the PR and should not be closed by the isolation slice alone."
  "2026-07-07T09:44:05.584Z",codex-agent,"Package lifecycle primitive update: pm-6abs promotes doctor isolation as a first-class lifecycle primitive across CLI flags, shell completion, help, SDK contract metadata, and action/tool schemas."
  "2026-07-07T16:42:43.496Z",codex-agent,"Implementation start: continuing SDK-first package/extension lifecycle promotion as one PR bundle linked to pm-usfg, pm-w89s, pm-cbwg, and pm-tnud. Live duplicate check used pm search --status all; closed read/lifecycle primitives pm-rjqr/pm-98cz/pm-395t are shipped and not reopened."
  "2026-07-07T17:44:32.221Z",codex-agent,"Evidence: promoted package/extension lifecycle primitives into the public SDK via PmClient and top-level helpers; exported ExtensionCommandResult/Options and UpgradeResult/Options; documented SDK lifecycle usage; added focused SDK package lifecycle tests. Verification passed: pnpm typecheck, pnpm lint, pnpm quality:docs-skills, pnpm test:coverage (5455 tests, 100/100/100/100), pnpm changelog:pm:check (pm-changelog 2026.7.6, CHANGELOG unchanged), pnpm audit --audit-level high (no known vulnerabilities), pm health --check-only --summary (ok), pm validate history drift ok with pre-existing closed-item resolution warnings. Manual temp tarball install passed SDK packageList/package/catalog/doctor/upgrade proof."
  "2026-07-07T18:07:11.472Z",codex-agent,"Review evidence: pre-push Greptile review cb62f157 flagged two SDK/gate polish issues; fixed both by making packageDoctor options-only at the public SDK call site and renaming mixed expected Sentry exemptions to ignored_expected_handled_*. Follow-up Greptile reviews 6ce1e4da and 1a754263 returned no review comments; also enforced package vocabulary after caller options so pm.package(...) cannot be downgraded to extension vocabulary."
  "2026-07-07T18:15:04.459Z",codex-agent,"Final verification evidence before PR: pnpm test:coverage passed 265 files / 5455 tests with 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines; temp tarball install in /tmp verified SDK packageList/package/packageLifecycle/catalog/packageDoctor/upgrade through @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk; pm health ok with warning_count=0; pm validate history drift ok with only pre-existing closed-item resolution warnings."
  "2026-07-07T18:36:09.019Z",codex-agent,"Review follow-up: Gemini suggested enforcing package vocabulary across all package lifecycle SDK paths. Fixed the SDK alias resolver so package-* action aliases force vocabulary=package after merging caller options, covering lower-level runAction/client.run calls in addition to PmClient.package(...). Added regression coverage with a conflicting vocabulary override on package-describe. Verification passed: focused SDK package lifecycle test, pnpm typecheck, pnpm lint, and pnpm test:coverage 5455 tests with 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-07T19:07:37.793Z",codex-agent,"Review follow-up evidence: addressed CodeRabbit/Cubic package-contract feedback by exporting PackageCommandOptions/PackageCommandResult and using them across package lifecycle helpers; cleaned pm-x6jf linked evidence so Sentry gate artifacts remain owned by pm-w86l; created/closed/released child slice pm-kffw so pm-changelog includes the implemented SDK feature. Verification after fixes passed: pnpm typecheck, pnpm lint, pnpm audit --audit-level high, pnpm quality:docs-skills, pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.7.6, pnpm test:coverage 5455 tests with 100/100/100/100, pnpm build, pm health warning_count=0, pm validate history drift ok with only pre-existing closed-item resolution warnings, pnpm sentry:telemetry:gate best-effort ok, and installed-package temp proof for package list/catalog/doctor/vocabulary guard/upgrade."
  "2026-07-07T19:23:41.764Z",codex-agent,"Bot review follow-up: Gemini identified that direct SDK calls to action=package could still pass vocabulary=extension because the guard only covered action aliases. Fixed resolveSdkActionInput to force vocabulary=package whenever the resolved action is package, including client.run/runAction direct paths, and added regression coverage for client.run(\"package\", { target: \"missing-package\", options: { describe: true, vocabulary: \"extension\" } }). Verification passed: focused SDK lifecycle test, pnpm typecheck, pnpm lint, and pnpm test:coverage 5455 tests with 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-07T19:24:18.498Z",codex-agent,"Installed-package proof after direct package guard fix: packed current checkout, installed it into a fresh /tmp project, initialized sandbox PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH, imported @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk, and verified packageList, packageLifecycle list, packageCatalog, packageDoctor isolated, dry-run upgrade, and direct client.run(\"package\", { describe: true, vocabulary: \"extension\" }) still reports package vocabulary."
  "2026-07-07T19:43:55.235Z",codex-agent,"CodeRabbit follow-up: tightened the public lifecycle type-contract test to assert every picked field for ExtensionCommandResult, PackageCommandResult, and UpgradeResult instead of only action. Verification passed: focused SDK lifecycle test, pnpm typecheck, and pnpm lint."
  "2026-07-08T06:06:37.973Z",codex,"Evidence: GitHub hygiene was checked for this bundle: PR #481 is the active wide SDK/context primitives branch; Dependabot PRs #462/#465 remain separate; Dependabot and code-scanning alert APIs returned no open alerts."
  "2026-07-14T17:32:25.647Z",codex-root,"Bundle selection evidence 2026-07-14: all-status inventory (1811 items), full live metadata/history reads, and GitHub issue review identified the remaining package-lifecycle child pm-evav plus related host-contract issues pm-f38n, pm-albl, and pm-as4a. Only these five actively edited items are in_progress; broader SDK parents and unrelated open issues remain open/unclaimed."
  "2026-07-14T17:50:30.885Z",codex-root,"Implementation checkpoint: the wide host-contract bundle now spans public SDK output ownership, real CLI renderer parity, ordered long/short list-flag accumulation, and documented variadic end-of-options behavior. Focused tests pass; pnpm typecheck and the full strict lint/static quality stack pass with 100% source/export/member docstrings, zero duplicates, package-boundary compliance, and token-budget compliance. Full coverage and packed temp-package acceptance remain before close."
  "2026-07-14T17:59:38.916Z",codex-root,"Coverage gate finding: the first full run exposed the newly covered host-contract lines plus a pre-existing environment-sensitive claim-next author branch. The host lines received source-instrumented tests; claim-next now deterministically exercises explicit, environment, and unknown fallbacks in one isolated test. This is linked to closed coverage ADR pm-w13j rather than creating duplicate coverage work. Focused claim and ESLint checks pass; rerunning the mandatory literal 100% gate."
  "2026-07-14T18:05:32.055Z",codex-root,"Observability evidence: packed-package execution produced healthy local telemetry configuration and pm health warning_count=0. Live Sentry query found zero criticals and two actionable highs, both pre-existing external-extension issues already tracked by open/unclaimed pm-d4ns (PM-CLI-2B, one handled event on 2026.7.11) and pm-7n5a (PM-CLI-29); 17 expected handled events were filtered. Trace/log lists had no 24h/1h rows, so real-time transaction/log ingestion is not claimed."
  "2026-07-14T18:22:33.141Z",codex-root,"PR #561 review pass 1: Greptile correctly identified scalar Commander accumulator hardening and structural-marker collision risk; CodeRabbit correctly identified missing CHANGELOG.md pm docs links. The fix accepts scalar-or-array previous values, uses a collision-resistant versioned protocol value, adds regression assertions, and links CHANGELOG.md to all five represented items. Gemini, Sourcery, and CodeRabbit full-review capacity notices were external quota limits, not code findings."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T18:08:01.631Z",codex-root,"Dynamic extension list flags cross two parsers: Commander consumes declared options before loose argv reconciliation, so an empty loose-occurrence ledger must preserve Commander values rather than replace them. Public output ownership should use a structural marker so independently installed packages do not depend on shared class identity."
